Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs100\t(,\fs110)\frz1\fad(3000,500)\fsp0\fscx120\pos(960,800)\b0\shad0\bord0}地          球          脉          动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.08,0:00:34.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类总是愿意冒着生命危险 占领地球上最高的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Human beings venture into the highest parts of our planet at their peril.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.00,0:00:37.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人们或许认为只要登上顶峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some might think that by climbing a great mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.92,0:00:40.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,便能征服一座高山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they have somehow conquered it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.08,0:00:43.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 我们仅仅只是这里的拜访者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but we can only be visitors here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.64,0:00:49.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个冰封的异域世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is a frozen alien world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:55.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs125\fsp8\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1300)}雄       伟       高       山
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.88,0:01:03.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是另一种极端环境\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the other extreme -
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:06.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1100)\bord0\shad3}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.36,0:01:07.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上一处最低最热的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}one of the lowest hottest places on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.72,0:01:17.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的地势低于海平面100多米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's over a hundred metres below the level of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.48,0:01:20.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这里却在酝酿一座高山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But here a mountain is in gestation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.92,0:01:28.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些硫酸池暗示 地底深处正进行着大规模活动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pools of sulphuric acid are indications that deep underground there are titanic stirrings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.80,0:01:37.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是埃塞俄比亚境内的达纳吉尔凹地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the Danakil Depression in Ethiopia,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.24,0:01:40.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,位于地球表面的大裂谷内\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}lying within a colossal rent of the earth's surface
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.20,0:01:44.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的陆地板块在此互相分离\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where giant land masses are pulling away from one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.64,0:01:50.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,熔岩经过这条地壳裂缝涌上地表\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Lava rises to the surface through this crack in the crust
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.60,0:01:53.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,诞生了一连串年轻的火山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}creating a chain of young volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:06.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这座埃特阿雷火山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This one, Erta Ale,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.00,0:02:11.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是地球上现存持续喷发时间最长的火山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is today the longest continually erupting volcano on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.92,0:02:16.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,岩浆湖在此沸腾了100多年\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a lake of lava that has been molten for over a hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.40,0:02:34.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些相同的火山作用 也造就了埃塞俄比亚高原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These same volcanic forces also created Ethiopia's highlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.04,0:02:41.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,7000万年前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}70 million years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.04,0:02:47.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片土地像达纳吉尔凹地一样平坦深陷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this land was just as flat and as deep as the Danakil Depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.16,0:02:52.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,熔岩从地核中漫涌上来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Molten lava rising from the earth's core
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.32,0:02:56.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成了绵延500英里的巨大石丘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}forced up a huge dome of rock 500 miles wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.64,0:02:59.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是非洲屋脊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the roof of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:11.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,千万年后 雨水和冰川 已将岩石雕琢成尖峰与峡谷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Over millennia, rain and ice carved the rock into a landscape of spires and canyons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:20.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些将近3英里高的山峰顶上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These summits, nearly 3 miles up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:24.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,住着一些非常特别的山地居民\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are home to some very remarkable mountaineers -
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.36,0:03:27.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮尾狒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Gelada baboons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.60,0:03:31.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是埃塞俄比亚高原的特有物种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They are unique to the highlands of Ethiopia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.92,0:03:48.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们睡觉的悬崖只有 攀岩高手才能爬得上去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cliffs where they sleep are for expert climbers only,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:51.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而狮尾狒则有一套合适的“工具”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and Gelado certainly have the right equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.64,0:03:53.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,强壮的手指是最主要的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the strongest fingers of any primate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.96,0:03:56.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然也少不了无所畏惧的气概\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and an utterly fearless disposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.48,0:04:03.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过在这样的高度  要想活下去可不太容易\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But you need more than a head for heights to survive up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.72,0:04:08.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下面将向你展示狮尾狒全天的生活  看看它们如何面对挑战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A day in a Gelado's life reveals how they've risen to the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.88,0:04:25.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于所有猴子来说  早晨正是“梳妆打扮”的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For all monkeys morning is grooming time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:28.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个交朋友的绝好机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a chance to catch up with friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.84,0:04:30.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 与其它猴子不同的是\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But, unlike other monkeys,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.88,0:04:34.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮尾狒一边这么做 一边还不停地唠叨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Gelados chatter constantly while they do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.88,0:04:39.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样手在忙活的同时也能搞好“人际关系”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a great way to network while your hands are busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:43.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这种社交活动不会很长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But these socials can't go on for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:46.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮尾狒全天的日程表排得很满\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Gelados have a busy daily schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.60,0:04:48.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有很多事情要做\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and there's work to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.56,0:04:54.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大部分猴类都无法在此生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most monkeys couldn't live up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.96,0:04:57.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里没有食物 可以吃的昆虫也很少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's no food and few insects to feed on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.84,0:04:59.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是狮尾狒却很特别\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But Gelados are unique -
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.64,0:05:04.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是世界上唯一完全以草为生的猴子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they're the only monkeys in the world that live almost entirely on grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.20,0:05:18.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们生活的社群是所有猴类中最大的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They live in the largest assemblies formed by any monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.04,0:05:21.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的甚至能达到800只\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some groups are 800 strong
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.28,0:05:25.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如同散布在高山草场上的角马群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they crop the high meadows like herds of wildebeest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.24,0:05:40.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,站在狮尾狒身旁的是西敏羱羊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Gelados graze alongside Walia ibex,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.68,0:05:43.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们也是这片高原的特有物种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which are also unique to these highlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.60,0:05:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种罕见的动物通常很胆小\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These rare creatures are usually very shy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.48,0:05:54.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但只要狮尾狒一来到身边  它们便放松警惕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they drop their guard when the Gelados are around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.28,0:06:01.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你或许会认为食草动物 总是尽量互相避让\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}You might expect that grazers would avoid each other's patch
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.60,0:06:05.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这种特殊联盟能使双方都得到好处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but this is a special alliance from which both partners benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.60,0:06:09.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们可以毫无顾虑地埋头吃草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's not so risky to put your head down
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.44,0:06:11.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为旁边有站岗的“哨兵”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}if others are on the lookout.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.48,0:06:15.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,西门豺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Ethiopian wolves -
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.40,0:06:18.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们一般不会在大白天发动进攻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they won't attempt an attack in broad daylight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.44,0:06:27.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是一到傍晚 高原便成了 一个危机四伏的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But at dusk the plateau becomes a more dangerous place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:31.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吃草活动基本结束\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the grazing largely over
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:37.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮尾狒们抓住最后一点机会进行社交  然后返回睡觉的悬崖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there's a last chance to socialise before returning to the sleeping cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.28,0:06:59.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,“即时预警系统”使大家都警觉起来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An early warning system puts everyone on the alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.60,0:07:54.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一天结束了 和开始时一样  它们又坐在了陡峭而安全的悬崖上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their day ends as it began, safe on the steep cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.68,0:08:04.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,埃塞俄比亚的火山正处于休眠期\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Ethiopian volcanoes are dormant,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.68,0:08:08.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是其它地方的火山仍在怒吼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but elsewhere others still rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.92,0:08:25.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火山构成了地球上最长山系的主干\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Volcanoes form the backbone of the longest mountain chain on our planet -
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.64,0:08:28.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南美洲的安第斯山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Andes of South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.20,0:08:36.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这座巨大的山脉 从赤道向南极绵亘5000英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This vast range stretches 5,000 miles from the Equator down to the Antarctic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.40,0:08:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的形成是由于太平洋板块\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It formed as the floor of the Pacific Ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.12,0:08:44.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,俯冲到南美洲板块之下  造成它的边缘隆起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}slid beneath the South American continent, buckling its edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.60,0:09:00.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最南端矗立着巴塔哥尼亚山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the southern end stand the mountains of Patagonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.28,0:09:03.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在是盛夏时节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's high summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.20,0:09:13.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是安第斯山的天气 是全球山区气候中最不稳定的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the Andes have the most unstable mountain weather on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.64,0:09:16.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暴风雪会在毫无征兆的情况下来袭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and storms can erupt without warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.32,0:09:19.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,气温直线下降\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Temperatures plummet
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:24.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,羊驼和它们新生的幼仔 只好忍受突如其来的风雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and guanacos and their newborn young must suddenly endure a blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.92,0:09:41.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以说是在一天之中度过了四季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Truly, all seasons in one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.08,0:09:54.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美洲狮\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A puma -
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.20,0:09:56.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,安第斯山区的狮子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the lion of the Andes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.64,0:10:06.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美洲狮通常独来独往 隐秘莫测\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pumas are usually solitary and secretive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.68,0:10:12.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这么一大家子在光天化日之下 外出实属罕见\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To see a group walking boldly in the open is extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.76,0:10:26.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个家庭由一只母狮和4只小狮组成\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a family - a mother with four cubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.88,0:10:33.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母狮只能利用这个短暂的夏天 教会小狮在山区生存的技能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She has just one brief summer in which to teach them their mountain survival techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.96,0:10:50.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把4只小狮养到这么大 是很了不起的业绩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Rearing four cubs to this age is an exceptional feat,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.76,0:10:53.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为它有一片富饶的领地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but she does have an excellent territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.16,0:10:55.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,食物和水都很充足\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}rich in food and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.04,0:11:01.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然小狮已长到和它们的母亲差不多大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Although the cubs are now as large as their mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.60,0:11:04.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们仍需要依靠母狮获取食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they still rely on her for their food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:31.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小狮至少还需要一年时间 才能学会独自狩猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It will be another year before the cubs can hunt for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.80,0:12:44.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果没有母狮的技术和经验\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Without their mother's skill and experience
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.76,0:12:47.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们肯定无法活过第一个冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they would never survive their first winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.24,0:13:12.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,凛冽的山风在崖坡上呼啸肆虐  生命根本无法在此扎根\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Battered by hurricane force winds, these slopes are now lifeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.96,0:13:19.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在更远的北方 它们还潜藏着其它危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Further north, they hold other dangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.72,0:13:56.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪崩时速可达250英里/小时  足以摧毁路过的一切\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Moving at 250 miles an hour, an avalanche destroys everything in its path.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.40,0:14:18.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,位于美国的落基山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the American Rockies
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.40,0:14:23.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每年冬季会发生10万次毁灭性的雪崩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a 100,000 avalanches devastate the slopes every winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.16,0:14:34.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的山系脊梁从巴塔哥尼亚 一直延伸到阿拉斯加\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This huge mountain chain continues the great spine that runs from Patagonia to Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:55.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管落基山地荒凉凄冷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The slopes of the Rockies, bleak though they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.08,0:14:58.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,却能为一些动物提供越冬场所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}provide a winter refuge for some animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.52,0:15:04.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,灰熊妈妈正走出巢穴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A mother grizzly emerges from her den
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.24,0:15:07.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长达6个月的地下冬眠结束了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}after six months' dozing underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:09.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两只小熊紧跟着它们的母亲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her two cubs follow her
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.28,0:15:12.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一次踏足这个陌生的户外世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and take their first steps in the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.52,0:15:30.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些陡峭的斜坡也是小熊的庇护所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These steep slopes provide a sanctuary for the cubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.04,0:15:33.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,公熊只要有机会就会吃掉它们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A male bear would kill and eat them given the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.88,0:15:37.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过大型动物很难爬到这个地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But big animals find it difficult to get about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.28,0:15:39.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,公熊体型可能是母熊的2倍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Males may be twice the size of a female
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:42.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但即使是母熊也已是举步艰难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and even she can have problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.00,0:16:01.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是它的幼崽在雪地里却是轻松自如  体型也和一般动物差不多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her cubs, however, make light of the snow and of life in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.68,0:16:17.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母熊面临着一个进退两难的选择\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the mother faces a dilemma:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.28,0:16:19.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它已经6个月没有吃东西了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it's six months since she last fed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.00,0:16:22.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的乳汁也即将耗尽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and her milk is starting to run dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.28,0:16:26.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它必须尽快离开这个安全的斜坡“托儿所”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She must soon leave the safety of these nursery slopes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.48,0:16:29.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把它的幼崽带离山地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and lead her cubs away from the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.84,0:16:34.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,若是稍有耽搁 整个家族就会面临饥荒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If she delays, the whole family will risk starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.20,0:17:05.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夏天揭露了落基山的真实面目\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Summer reveals the true nature of the Rockies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.36,0:17:14.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剥去雪层之后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Stripped of snow,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.92,0:17:18.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,山峰裸露出斧凿般的造型\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the peaks bear their sculpted forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.20,0:17:25.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,山地动物只有此时才能 向更高的地方拓展疆土\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Only now can mountaineers reclaim the upper reaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.08,0:18:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两英里高的碎石崖上 似乎不可能有生命存在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Two miles up the crumbling precipices seem devoid of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.28,0:18:13.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是那里仍有动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But there are animals here -
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.08,0:18:33.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只灰熊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a grizzly bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.84,0:18:38.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很奇怪这样的动物为何 会爬到如此高的碎石斜坡上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It seems to be an odd creature to find on these high rocky slopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.84,0:18:45.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真不知道这里有什么吸引着它\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's hard to imagine what could have attracted it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.36,0:19:05.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在每年的这个时候  熊必须为越冬储备脂肪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At this time of the year bears should be fattening up for the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.24,0:19:10.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而却有一定数量的灰熊 聚集在这片不毛之地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet they gather in some numbers on these apparently barren slopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.80,0:19:25.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们正在寻找一种很特别的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're searching for a rather unusual food -
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.28,0:19:28.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞蛾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}moths.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.72,0:19:32.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了躲避低洼地带的炎热  数百万只飞蛾抵达此地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Millions have flown up here to escape the heat of the lowlands
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.20,0:19:34.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,栖身于岩石缝隙之中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they're now roosting among the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:41.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞蛾似乎并不足以填饱熊的肚子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Moths may seem a meager meal for a bear,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.16,0:19:43.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们身体内富含脂肪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but their bodies are rich in fat
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.08,0:19:47.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直接关系到灰熊每年冬天的生存能力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and can make all the difference in a bear's annual struggle for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.88,0:19:53.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里又开辟了一个新的战场\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Another battle is being waged here
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.44,0:19:56.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是不会持续多久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but on a much longer timescale.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.36,0:20:00.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些散落的石块是从山脊上崩裂下来的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These loose boulders are the mountain's crumbling bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.84,0:20:03.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,落基山脉已不再上升\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Rockies are no longer rising
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.16,0:20:05.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,却是在慢慢地崩塌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but slowly disintegrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.44,0:20:16.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界各地的高山都在不断经受 森林、积雪和冰川的消蚀\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All mountains everywhere are being worn down by frost, snow and ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.60,0:20:25.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔卑斯山崛起于1500万年前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Alps were raised some 15 million years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.04,0:20:31.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原因是非洲板块向北漂移  与欧洲南麓相撞\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}as Africa, drifting northwards, collided with the southern edge of Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.92,0:20:44.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曾经连接两块大陆的古老海床 侵蚀后留下了一座座尖耸的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These spires are the eroded remains of an ancient seabed that once stretched between the two continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.04,0:21:04.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是这些只是阿尔卑斯山麓地带的小山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But these are just the Alpine foothills.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.76,0:21:08.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,山脉中心地带的山峰伫立高达3英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The range at its centre rises to 3 miles high
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.96,0:21:12.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且终年覆盖积雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and is crowned with permanent snows.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.16,0:21:26.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,马特洪峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Matterhorn,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.40,0:21:30.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高峻挺拔的峰顶甚至无法附着积雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}its summit too steep to hold a snow field.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.48,0:21:42.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,勃朗峰——西欧最高的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mont Blanc - the highest peak in Western Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.24,0:21:58.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔卑斯山峰具有与众不同的尖齿状外形\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The distinctive jagged shapes of the Alps
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.56,0:22:02.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些杰作出自一位伟大的山峰雕刻家之手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}were carved by those great mountain sculptors -
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.08,0:22:03.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰川\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the glaciers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.48,0:22:11.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一望无际的流动冰河\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Immense rivers of moving ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.04,0:22:13.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,满载着岩石\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}laden with rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.44,0:22:15.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,碾磨出一座座尖峭的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}grind their way down the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.96,0:22:18.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,刨削出一个个深邃的山谷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}gouging out deep valleys.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.92,0:22:29.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是地球上最大的侵蚀作用\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the most powerful erosive force on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.24,0:22:44.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰川瓯穴——由冰融水凿成的 直达冰川深处的圆筒状竖井\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A moulin - a shaft in the ice opened by melt water as it plunges into the depths of the glacier.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.52,0:23:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正如奔腾不息的流水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Like the water running through it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.16,0:23:03.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰川也在不断移动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the ice itself is constantly moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.92,0:23:07.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一刻不停地刨蚀着深谷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}flowing down the valley with unstoppable force.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.76,0:23:28.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔卑斯冰川看起来已是无边无际\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Alpine glaciers may seem immense,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.24,0:23:34.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它仍比不上分隔印度次大陆 和西藏的巨大山脉中的冰川\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they're dwarfed by those in the great ranges that divide the Indian subcontinent from Tibet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.84,0:23:47.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片巨石滩嘴属于巨大的巴尔托洛冰川  位于巴基斯坦境内的喀喇昆仑山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the boulder strewn snout of the giant Baltoro glacier in the Karakoram mountains of Pakistan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.12,0:23:59.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是地球上最大的山丘冰川\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's the biggest mountain glacier on Earth -
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.12,0:24:02.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长43英里 宽3英里多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}43 miles long and over 3 miles wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.00,0:24:06.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这座冰封山谷巨大无比\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This huge ice-filled valley is so large
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.44,0:24:09.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使在太空中也能看得很清楚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it's clearly visible from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.32,0:24:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是地球上5英里以上高峰最集中的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the greatest concentration of peaks over 5 miles high to be found anywhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.28,0:24:44.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是最危险的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the most dangerous mountains of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.44,0:24:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乔戈里峰和它的姊妹峰夺去的生命 比其它山峰都要多得多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}K2 and her sister peaks have claimed more lives than any others.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.28,0:25:04.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的山峰极为险峻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The peaks here rise so precipitously,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.44,0:25:07.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰川陡峭易碎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the glaciers are so steep and crevassed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.08,0:25:12.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,纵使最有经验的登山运动员 也很难征服这些高山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that few except the most skilled mountaineers can penetrate these ranges.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.72,0:25:19.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,捻角山羊正在举行年度聚会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Markhor gather for their annual rut.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.04,0:25:34.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,公羊必须为争夺生育权而战斗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Males must fight for the right to breed,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.12,0:25:38.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在如此峻峭的崖壁上  哪一方滑倒都有可能直接送命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but on these sheer cliffs any slip by either animal could be fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.04,0:25:51.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A snow leopard -
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.28,0:25:53.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喜马拉雅地区最稀有的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the rarest of Himalayan animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.92,0:25:58.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是只母豹 正要返回巢穴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a female returning to her lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.52,0:26:14.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是在野外环境中 第一次近距离拍摄雪豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are the first intimate images of snow leopard ever filmed in the wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.96,0:26:27.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在向自己一岁大的幼崽问好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She greets her one year old cub.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.04,0:26:33.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的巢穴选址不错\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her den is well chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.40,0:26:37.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常适于观望周围崖壁的情况\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It has exceptional views of the surrounding cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.32,0:26:42.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这些变化莫测的悬崖上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}On these treacherous slopes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.60,0:26:45.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有其它掠食者能和雪豹一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}no hunter other than the snow leopard
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.20,0:26:48.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有机会逮住这些羸弱的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}would have a chance of catching such fragile prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.36,0:26:59.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只母羊和几只小羊羔 是最容易下手的目标\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A female with young makes an easier target.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.40,0:27:20.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它那宽大的脚爪具备很好的抓地力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her large paws give an excellent grip
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.48,0:27:23.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长尾巴能保持身体平衡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that long tail helps her balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.76,0:27:37.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它静悄悄地来到猎物上方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Silently she positions herself above her prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.36,0:28:40.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一次它无功而返\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She returns with nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.32,0:29:15.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金雕在悬崖边巡视  搜寻着老弱病残的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Golden eagles patrol these cliffs in search of the weak or injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.40,0:29:37.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,靠着两米长的翼展\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With a 2 metre wing span
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.72,0:29:41.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些大鸟能轻松抓起一只小羊羔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this bird could easily take a young markhor.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.60,0:29:46.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金雕捕猎靠的是视力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eagles hunt by sight
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.36,0:29:50.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪越下越密 它们只好选择放弃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the thickening veil of snow forces them to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.16,0:30:09.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过雪却能为雪豹提供掩护\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For the leopard the snow provides cover
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.40,0:30:11.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使它有机会捕猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and creates an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.24,0:30:33.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恶劣的天气掩盖了它逼近的脚步声\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The worsening weather dampens the sound of her approach
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.20,0:30:36.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它正逐渐进入攻击范围\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}allowing her to get within striking distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.84,0:30:55.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它已被逼上了绝路\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It was an act of desperation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.92,0:30:58.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以才会捕捉如此大的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to try and catch such a large animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.80,0:31:09.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狼刚进行完一场屠杀\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Wolves have made a kill
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.92,0:31:13.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为其它掠食者留下了残存的肢体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}giving other hunters a chance to scavenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.00,0:31:32.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,肆虐的风雪终于使雪豹成功了一回\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The worst of the blizzard brings success for the snow leopard,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.64,0:31:35.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过作为自古以来的狩猎方式\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but having descended so far to make the kill
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.36,0:31:39.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它得费很大气力才能把猎物拖回家中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}she has a grueling climb to get back to her lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.08,0:31:55.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小豹只能耐心等待\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cub must be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.12,0:32:01.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它至少需要一年时间才能有足够的技巧和力量 在这些艰险的峭壁上独自狩猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It'll be a year before it has the strength and skill to kill for itself on these difficult slopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.88,0:32:29.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪豹是一种几乎被神化了的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The snow leopard is an almost mythical creature,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.48,0:32:31.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是荒野的标志\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}an icon of the wilderness,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.48,0:32:34.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种动物只有很少一部分人亲眼见过\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}an animal few humans have ever glimpsed
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.48,0:32:38.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们很少涉足它们的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for its world is one we seldom visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.60,0:32:48.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喀喇昆仑座落在另一座山脉的西侧\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Karakoram lie at the western end of a range
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.92,0:32:52.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这座山脉绵延长达地球圆周的1/10\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that stretches across a tenth of our planet -
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.16,0:32:54.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它就是喜马拉雅山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.76,0:33:07.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些世界上最高的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These, the highest mountains of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.64,0:33:09.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与其它大型山脉一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}like other great ranges,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.64,0:33:13.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是由于大陆板块相撞而形成的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}were created by the collision of continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.88,0:33:17.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约5千万年前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some 50 million years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.08,0:33:19.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,印度次大陆撞上西藏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}India collided with Tibet
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.16,0:33:24.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,挤压形成的这些巨大山峰 至今仍在不断升高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}thrusting up these immense peaks, which are still rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.80,0:33:36.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这条岩石与冰川组成的巨幅屏障极其宽广  甚至能改变全球气候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This vast barrier of rock and ice is so colossal it shapes the world's climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.88,0:33:40.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,印度吹来的暖风满载着水气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Warm winds from India, full of moisture,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.92,0:33:43.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经由喜马拉雅山脉抬升\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are forced upwards by the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.28,0:33:45.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上升的气流逐渐变冷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the air rises so it cools,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.84,0:33:48.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成云团\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}causing clouds to form
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.08,0:33:50.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而产生了季风雨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the monsoon is born.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.64,0:34:31.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高海拔地区的季风雨变成了雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At high altitudes the monsoon rains fall as snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.96,0:34:36.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是中国境内的山脉东部起点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, at the far eastern end of the range in China,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.40,0:34:41.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一位居民在户外忍受着严冬的寒冷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}one inhabitant endures the bitter winters out in the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.24,0:34:52.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在其它大部分熊都已躲在地下睡大觉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most other bears would be sleeping underground by now,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.32,0:34:57.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是大熊猫没能储备足够的脂肪冬眠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the giant panda can't fatten up enough to hibernate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.68,0:35:03.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它完全依赖竹子为生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Its food, bamboo, on which it totally relies
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.80,0:35:06.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是竹叶没有太多营养价值\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has so little nutritional value
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.60,0:35:10.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它无法像别的熊那样积累起脂肪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that it can't build up a store of fat like other bears.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.00,0:35:16.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的大部分动物 都随着季节变化上下迁移\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most of the creatures here move up or down the slopes with the seasons
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.60,0:35:19.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有大熊猫因为食物始终逗留此地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the panda is held captive by its diet
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.64,0:35:24.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它吃的这种竹子只生长在这一海拔地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for the kind of bamboo it eats only grows at this altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.24,0:35:36.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过这些森林对于更灵活的动物来说 却没有什么挑战性\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But these forests hold fewer challenges for the more mobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.32,0:35:45.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和大熊猫一样  川金丝猴只生活在中国境内\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The golden snap-nosed monkey, like the giant panda, lives only in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.88,0:35:52.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们有厚实的毛发  所以能比其它猴类更能适应高海拔气候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their thick fur allows them to survive at greater altitudes than any other monkey
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.92,0:35:57.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每当严寒袭来  这些山坡就成了它们的天下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and when the cold bites they have these upper slopes to themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.20,0:36:07.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然有了暖和的“大衣”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even if you have a warm coat
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.12,0:36:11.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最好还是与尽可能多的伙伴 挤在一起保暖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it apparently helps to surround yourself with as many layers as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.88,0:36:16.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些猴子至少还有一个选择\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But at least these monkeys have a choice -
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.28,0:36:19.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果它们厌倦了树皮和其它残存的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}if they tire of tree bark and other survival food
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.72,0:36:23.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,便会搬迁到温暖的低海拔地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they can always descend to lower warmer altitudes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.08,0:36:25.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等到春天再返回此地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and not return there till spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.56,0:36:31.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰雪消融\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the snows retreat
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.76,0:36:34.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,万木逢春\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}trees come into bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.96,0:36:41.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,樱花\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Cherry blossom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.44,0:36:45.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杜鹃花\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Rhododendrons -
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.88,0:36:49.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在大自然中形成大片灌木林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}here in their natural home they form great forests
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.16,0:36:52.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为这幅季候风景画抹上一笔浓艳的色彩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and fill the landscape with the covers of a new season.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.88,0:37:17.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些灌木林也是许多种春季候鸟的家园\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These forests are a host to a rich variety of springtime migrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.72,0:37:34.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,花丛下别有一番景象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Beneath the blooms - another display.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.24,0:37:41.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在正是亚洲雉的交配季节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's the mating season for oriental pheasants,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.64,0:37:43.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,棕尾虹雉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Himalayan monal,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.12,0:37:48.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,角雉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}tragopan
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.68,0:37:50.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有血雉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and blood pheasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.52,0:38:03.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,许多春季食物才刚露面不久  便已被麝鹿一扫而光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Musk deer make the most of a short flash of spring foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.16,0:38:09.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只公鹿闻到了未来配偶的气味\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This male smells a potential mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.60,0:38:27.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小熊猫在野外十分罕见\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The red panda, rarely glimpsed in the wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.16,0:38:29.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它曾经被认为是浣熊的一种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It was once considered a kind of raccoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.68,0:38:33.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在已被确认为一种小型山地熊类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but is now believed to be a small mountain bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.72,0:38:50.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到了仲夏 它那更大更有名的亲戚 便会躲进山洞\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By midsummer its larger, more famous relative, has retreated into a cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.72,0:39:09.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只大熊猫正在照顾刚满一周的小宝宝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A giant panda nurses a tiny week old baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.32,0:39:19.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,轻柔的清洁是为了防止感染\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her tender cleaning wards off infection.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.52,0:39:34.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,未来3周内 它都不会离开这个山洞\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She won't leave this cave for three weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.00,0:39:39.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,否则它的幼崽将彻底无依无靠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}not while her cub is so utterly helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.72,0:39:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幼崽生长得很慢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Progress is slow
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.44,0:39:55.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为由竹子转化来的乳汁少得可怜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for milk produced on a diet of bamboo is wretchedly poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.24,0:40:06.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小家伙已经4周大了 可仍旧看不见东西\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Four weeks old and the cub is still blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.40,0:40:20.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到出生后的第3个月  它的眼睛才能完全睁开\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Its eyes do not fully open until three months after birth,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.08,0:40:24.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是熊猫幼崽长到成年的机会极为渺茫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the chances of the cub reaching adulthood are slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.12,0:40:32.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大熊猫努力养育幼崽的情景\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The struggle of a giant panda mother to raise her cub
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.68,0:40:38.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真是大山里濒危生命求生的动人一幕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is a touching symbol of the precariousness of life in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.36,0:40:51.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球上最高的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}On the highest summits of our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.32,0:40:53.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有什么生物能在此永久生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}nothing can live permanently.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.24,0:40:59.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界上最高的山峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The highest peak of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.88,0:41:08.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海拔5.5英里的世界屋脊 ——珠穆朗玛峰仍在不断升高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mount Everest, five and a half miles above sea level and still rising - the roof of our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.56,0:41:12.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在试图登顶珠峰的人中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Of those humans who've tried to climb it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.40,0:41:15.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有1/10失去了生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}one in ten have lost their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.48,0:41:21.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而成功的人们也只能在峰顶短暂逗留\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Those that succeed can stand for only a few moments on its summit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.24,0:41:27.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尼泊尔人称之为 “一座高得连鸟也飞不上去的山峰”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Nepalese call it 'a mountain so high no bird can fly above it.'
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.52,0:41:42.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是 5万多只蓑羽鹤每年都会 进行一场地球上最具挑战性的迁徙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But each year over 50,000 demoiselle cranes set out on one of the most challenging migrations on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.72,0:41:47.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要想到达印度境内的越冬场所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To reach their overwintering grounds in India
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.96,0:41:51.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须跨越喜马拉雅山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they must cross the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.60,0:42:01.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,晌午时分 群山间狂风大作\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By late morning ferocious winds are roaring past the peaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.88,0:42:06.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鹤群必须提升高度  躲避正在形成的风暴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cranes must gain height to avoid the building storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.56,0:42:37.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们遇上了一股强力气旋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They've hit serious turbulence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.88,0:42:43.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们只好掉头返回\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They must turn back
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.64,0:42:45.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,否则就会送命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or risk death.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.52,0:43:21.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新的一天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A new day
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.12,0:43:23.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新的机遇\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and a new opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.52,0:43:28.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鹤群通过互相鸣叫保持密切联系\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The flock stay in close contact by calling one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.88,0:43:40.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管它们缺食少水 日渐衰弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Weak from lack of food and water,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.08,0:43:45.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可它们会利用热空气 ——呈圆柱形上升的热气流来获取高度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they use thermals, rising columns of warm air, to gain height.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.96,0:44:06.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,许多蓑羽鹤都是第一次 踏上穿越喜马拉雅的旅程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For many this is their first journey across the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.84,0:44:10.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而有些却是最后一次\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For some, it will be their last.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.64,0:44:21.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金雕早已企待它们的到来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The golden eagles have been expecting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.24,0:44:37.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两只金雕合作将一只小鹤 从队伍中分离出来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The eagles work in pairs to separate a young crane from the flock.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.08,0:45:24.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它躲过了其中一只的追捕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It escapes the touches of one,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.60,0:45:26.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,却没能逃过另一只的利爪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and is caught by another.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.64,0:45:33.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只小鹤的份量也是挺重的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But even a young crane is a heavy prize
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.24,0:45:36.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金雕不得不努力控制飞行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the eagle has to struggle to control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.48,0:45:57.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母鹤可不能等得太久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The mother can wait no longer -
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.40,0:46:01.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一场与恶劣气候的死亡赛跑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this is a desperate race against worsening weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.80,0:46:10.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鹤群其它成员开始背水一战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The rest of the flock battle on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.68,0:46:20.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上升过程中每扇一下翅膀 都得用尽全身气力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the ascent every wing beat becomes an exhausting struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.12,0:46:43.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后它们终于翻越了旅途中最高的障碍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At last they are over the highest barrier that lies in their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.80,0:46:54.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 与所有高山世界的拜访者一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But like all who visit the world of the high mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.84,0:46:57.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们也不敢逗留\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they dare not linger.

